streaming findall solutions
lazy list
int ids instead of string names, this will increase the string pool
bump allocator + container_of for variable-size terms (const 16B, var 16B, func 96B, string 16B -> ~75% pool reduction)

- arithmetic: bitwise ops (>>, <<, \/, /\)
- readline/history in repl
- assert/1 as alias for assertz/1 is missing

- if there are more than one "_" named anonymus variable in the eval scope, they are going to unify.
- trailing unparseable input in a query is silently ignored instead of erroring (e.g. ?- X is 5 \/ 3 gives X = 5)

